		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9757 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.68]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">Debalic wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><blockquote><b id="fs8">dracoboars wrote:</b><hr size="1" /><b>Necros</b> and beastlords like to run off at the mouth but the bottom line is they <b>can only kill one mob at a time</b> so why are you quading four for them? <hr size="1" /></blockquote><br>Really? I must be doing something wrong then! [:laugh:]<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Fighting 4 mobs at once is not the same as *killing*&nbsp;&nbsp;4 mobs at once...<br><br>The assumption in quadding is that you are killing 4 mobs just as effectively as one. Since AE spells will hit up to 4 mobs, it costs the exact same amount of mana/time to kill 4 as one. So one can kill *one* mob at a time, and calculate the time/mana it takes to kill that one, or use AEs and kill 4 at once redoing the calculation (since the AEs cost more mana per damage, but are vastly more effective if you've got four targets).<br><br>Engaging 4 mobs and killing them using single targetted spells is absolutely no more efficient then simply killing one at a time 4 times in a row. Same thing. In fact, it's generally going to be less efficient since you've got to manage 4 mobs at a time, but you still have to spend the same mana per mob you kill. If you've got 4 times the mana pool as that needed to single kill a mob, you can kill 4 at once. But you aren't really buying yourself anything, and you most certainly are not &quot;quad kiting&quot;.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
